 Fix the Neo4j Connection
First, check if your Neo4j Docker container is running.

Open a new terminal (not a project terminal).

Run the command: docker ps

Look for a container named maya-neo4j.

If you dont see it in the list, it means the container is stopped. Start it with this command:

Bash

docker start maya-neo4j
If it is running on "http://localhost:7474/browser/", double-check that the NEO4J_URI, NEO4J_USER, and NEO4J_PASSWORD in your backend/.env file are correct.

Username → neo4j

Password → password123


